# tkv2 - select-reactive: reactive-options variant of std-ui-select

Slice `select-from-signal` (`specs/std-ui-select.md` § "Reactive options
(selectFrom)"): `selectFrom` builds a `<select>` `TkNode` over a
`Signal[List[A]]` source (busi's motivating case: a fetched contracts list)
instead of a static `List[(String,String)]`. DOM serialization (the reactive
`<option>` reconciliation itself — item added/removed/reordered without a
page reload, preserving DOM node identity) is covered by
`JsRuntimeSelectFromTest.scala` (a real Node + real `signals.mjs` runtime
test, mirroring `JsRuntimeKeyedForTest.scala`'s method — conformance has no
DOM available on either lane, same as the base `select()`'s own
`tkv2-select.ssc`). This conformance file keeps the public API and the
`lower()` path live on both lanes, and exercises that mutating the source
signal (`items.set(...)`) and re-lowering does not throw.

[signal](std/ui/primitives.ssc)
[selectFrom](std/ui/input.ssc)
[lower](std/ui/lower.ssc)
[defaultTheme](std/ui/theme.ssc)

```scalascript
case class Contract(id: String, title: String)

val items = signal("tkv2SelectReactiveItems", [Contract("c1", "Alpha"), Contract("c2", "Beta")])
val picked = signal("tkv2SelectReactivePicked", "c2")

println(picked())
picked.set("c1")
println(picked())

// Safe named-arg calling convention (see specs/std-ui-select.md "Known
// limitation" — a bin/ssc-run-only standard-tier bug, not this lane).
val node = selectFrom(items, (c) => c.id, (c) => (c.id, c.title), picked,
                       label = "Pick a contract", placeholder = "Choose...", disabled = false)
val view = lower(node, defaultTheme)
println("select-from-built")

// The source signal changes after the tree is built — item appended. Proves
// the .ssc-level plumbing (constructing the reactive source, re-lowering)
// survives a list mutation without throwing; the actual DOM reconciliation
// this enables is verified by JsRuntimeSelectFromTest.scala (real DOM, real
// Node), not reachable from a conformance println-diff.
items.set([Contract("c1", "Alpha"), Contract("c2", "Beta"), Contract("c3", "Gamma")])
val view2 = lower(node, defaultTheme)
println("select-from-relowered")

// placeholder-only path: empty initial selection, disabled render.
val empty = signal("tkv2SelectReactiveEmpty", "")
val node2 = selectFrom(items, (c) => c.id, (c) => (c.id, c.title), empty,
                        label = "", placeholder = "Nothing yet", disabled = true)
val view3 = lower(node2, defaultTheme)
println("select-from-disabled-built")
```
